Comments: TORNADO OBSERVED MOVING ACROSS HIGHWAY 59 AND LIFTING ABOUT 5 NNE OF WAUBUN AROUND 349 PM CDT. TORNADO APPEARED TO PASS JUST SOUTH OF THE MAHNOMEN COUNTY AIRPORT. (FGF)
TORNADO TRACKED TO THE NORTH NORTHEAST FOR ABOUT 13 MILES. NUMEROUS TREES AND POWER POLES WERE SNAPPED ALONG THE PATH. FARM SHEDS WERE BLOWN DOWN AND MACHINERY FLIPPED. (FGF)
NEAR SAND HILL LAKE CLOSE TO MAHNOMEN/POLK COUNTY LINE BEBRIS WAS FALLING FROM CLOUD AS LAW ENFORCEMENT OBSERVED TORNAO LIFT BACK INTO CLOUD. (FGF)
AT LEAST TWO FUNNELS WERE SIGHTED EAST OF FRAZEE. A BRIEF TOUCHDOWN WAS OBSERVED IN AN OPENED AREA. (FGF)
ONE QUARTER MILE SW OF WILMAR WITH DEBRIS IN THE AIR. STILL ON THE GROUND MOVING EAST AT 15 MPH. (MPX)
APPROXIMATELY 200 YARDS WIDE. HIT A FARM AND PICKED UP A LARGE AMOUNT OF METAL DEBRIS. MOVING 40 TO 50 MPH TOWARD THE EAST. (MPX)
2 HOUSES HEAVILY DAMAGED ON SW 26TH AVE NEAR 40TH ST SE. (MPX)
OCCURRED NEAR HIGHWAY 40 AND JUST EAST OF COUNTY ROAD 7. (MPX)
